@node über "Characteristics"

  @{b}Which can do the program?@{ub}

Did you miss already once birthday, wedding day or another
important date? With BEKUNA that would not have happened!

BEKUNA is a useful aid in the everyday life. It reminds the user, when
switching on the computer, of highlights, birthdays, wedding day
and holidays. One has constantly an overview of the age of its
distorted and acquaintance and points, who is born on one Sunday and
under which asterisk. BEKUNA point also when the next holiday is and
when vacations are.
That is not yet everything! Bekuna can do still much more!
Nearly all procedures run fully automatically.

@{b}That knows BEKUNA:@{ub}

- greetings dependent on the time of day.
- current one announcement of date, time, summer time, asterisk, week and the mondphase as bars or diagram.
- computation of sunrise, sun highest level and sunset
- message from birthdays and different events.
- computation and message from holidays and anniversaries for each country.
  (many holiday files are contained)
- automatic change-over of the system clock on summer time and back.
- clock place over the InterNet (of atomic clock).
- data preview
- announcement of the next to last system start.
- data exchange with other AMIGA's
- manual data exchange with PEKUTER (pekuter.enkapeem.de)
- fully automatic data exchange with PEKUTER, if the Amiga on an emulator (e.g. WinUAE) runs

@{b}Characteristics:@{ub}

- sound messages to certain events.
- start of other programs, when the occurrence certain events.
- bubble help in the main window, adjusting window and input window.
- with all windows the size and/or the position can be fixed.
- calendars to the information and for the date input of events.
- fast calling buttons in the main window.
- many adjustment possibilities
- announcement and printing of all data.
- colored character indication
- picture announcement of persons
- waiting animation, Startlogo, mini pictures, moon diagram
- translation (German and English lies with)
- Bekuna can become iconify
- and much more besides...

BEKUNA is written in AREXX and uses AWNPIPE for the ReActionGUI.

@endnode
@node benötigt "Requirement"

  @{b}Which I need?@{ub}

- An Amiga with OS3.5 or more highly.
- RexxMast must run, of the Startup Sequence out.
- about 250 KB free space on the boot partition (SYS:)
- about 1-2 MB free RAM.
- mind. 68020 CCU

 @{u}Recommended:@{uu}

- OS3.9
- mind. 68030 50 MHz
- grafic card
- mind. 8 MB RAM

An Amiga with OS3.9 and Boingbag3.9-1 and Boingbag3.9-2 are ideal.

A sceen size, than 640x480 is not smaller to recommending!
Best a grafic card or a AGA DBLPAL flicker-free.
For a good announcement of the diagrams and pictures 256 colors are necessary (16 bits are better).

 @{u}@{b}NOTE!@{uu}@{ub}

It may not be installed ClassAct!

BEKUNA runs only correctly, with a completely installed operating system.
Also examine Startup Sequence! Path must the entries REXX: and SYS:Rexxc available its!

RexxMast must run, of the Startup Sequence or the user Startup.
It must the entry: SYS:System/REXXMast >NIL: or REXXMast >NIL: available its.

RexxMast must be in the drawer SYS:System. Not in the WBStartup!

See also: @{" What don't do runs correctly? " link problem}

@{u}Successful tested on the following computers:@{uu}

Amiga 2000
OS3.9 + BB1 + BB2
CPU 68060 50 MHz
100 MB FAST RAM
grafic card Cybervision64/3D (dissolution: 800x600 8 bits)

Development computer from version 1.0 to 1.95:
Amiga 4000 OS3.9 + BB1 + BB2
CPU 68040 25 MHz
16 MB FAST RAM
grafic card Cybervision64 (dissolution: 800x600 16 bits)

Development computer from version 2.0:
PC with WinUAE
Pentium IV 2.54 GHz
1 GB RAM
OS3.9 + BB1 + BB2
CPU 68040 approx 700 MHz
128 MB FAST RAM
emulated grafic card Picasso (dissolution: 1024x768 32 bits)

@endnode
@node install "Installation"

  @{b}Installation@{ub}

Doubleclick on "Installation" installs the program into the correct drawers.
Also for update installation!
Please also all installation assistance read!

  @{b}Which everything installed? (FULL VERSION 2.1)@{ub}

Bekuna-Autostart    --> WBStartup  |automatic start program|
Bekuna-Start        --> Sys:Tools  |manual start program|
Bekuna.rexx         --> REXX:      |main program|
BekunaPrefs         --> SYS:Prefs  |preferences|
ShowTx              --> REXX:      |text messages|
ShowPic             --> REXX:      |picture view|
ErrorMessage        --> REXX:      |error messages|
RequestRX           --> REXX:      |ask window yes/no|
RequestChoiceRX     --> REXX:      |ask window|
Warten.rexx         --> REXX:      |wait and gauge window|
Transdata.rexx      --> REXX:      |exchange data with PEKUTER|

Symbole.pic     --> REXX:Data  |mini picture|
Date.pic        --> REXX:Data  |mini calendar|
MondanimZ.pic   --> REXX:Data  |moon grafic 1|
MondanimA.pic   --> REXX:Data  |moon grafic 2|
Logo.pic        --> REXX:Data  |BEKUNA Logo|
WartAnim.pic    --> REXX:Data  |wait animation|
Pikto.info      --> REXX:Data  |iconify icon|
Holiday.xxxxx   --> REXX:Data  |holiday description for country|
HolidayEdit     --> REXX:Data  |holiday editor|

Background sample --> SYS:Prefs/Presets/BekunaPattern
Librarys          --> SYS:Libs
AWNPIPE           --> SYS:Devs
Catalogs          --> SYS:Locale/Catalogs

REXX: standard is the directory S:

@endnode
@node geschichte "History"

  @{b}The programming of BEKUNA@{ub}

I, in an at that time already old magazine, discovered 1994 a small, printed ARexx program. At the time I had no notion from ARexx still. I typed it and started it. It functioned.
It opened only a simple window, welcomed me and showed the date and the time. Two years later I inserted then a birthday message also. Thus I used it then by February 2002. At the 6.Feb.2002 me then the idea the program came to make nevertheless adjustable and also a ReAction surface use.
Thus still developed on the same day BEKUNA V1.0...

 @{b}@{u}The versions:@{ub}@{uu}

***** Bekuna begun to programming to 06.02.2002 *****

***** version 1.0 (06.02.2002) *****

- greetings dependent on the time of day.
- current one announcement of date, time, summer time, mondphase and asterisk.
- message from birthdays.
- ReAction GUI
- message from events.
- special messages
- computation and message of all holidays and many anniversaries for Germany.

***** version 1.1 (08.02.2002) *****

- past events
- holiday computation also for the following year.

***** first public version 1.2 (10.02.2002) *****

- automatic change-over on summer time and back.
- guidance
- installation

***** version 1.3 (07.03.2002) *****

- message of all events in the preliminary message period.
- automatic paging through, if several events arise.
- adjustable character sets.
- sound messages with certain events.
- start of programs, when the occurrence certain events.
- adjustable preliminary message period.
- speech blister assistance in the main and prefs window.
- alternatively a moon diagram can be used.
- with all windows the size and/or the position can be fixed.
- calendars only for information and for the date input of coming events.
- announcement of the weekdays in the list for coming events.
- faster one announcement of the holiday list.
- speed calling buttons in the main window.
- show the last system start.
- pictures: smily, moon diagram
- error corrections

***** version 1.4 (21.03.2002) *****

- input of recurring events (e.g. garbage disposal)
- announcement of the weekdays in all windows
- announcement of the weekdays to all messages
- announcement of age and asterisk in the birthday list
error corrections:
- moon diagram now also with OS3.5
- other...

***** version 1.5 (24.03.2002) *****

- error corrections with the data input

***** version 1.6 (02.05.2002) *****

- holiday computation for Germany, Austria and Switzerland
- error corrections with the data input and data correction
- error corrections with sound messages and program start
- system test
- example picture
- the program reads the attitudes from locale.prefs.

***** version 1.7 (14.05.2002) *****

- improved systematical test
- improved start of programs
- error corrections

***** version 1.8 (15.05.2002) *****

- expressions of all data

***** version 1.9 (21.05.2002) *****

- data preview
- progress announcement
- safe against errors
- improved system test

***** version 1.94 (04.06.2002) *****

- the main window can be updated over the menu.
- adjust the computer clock over the InterNet
- iconify

***** version 1.95 (20.06.2002) *****

- improved character set adjuster

***** version 2.0 (24.01.2004) *****

- international version
- languages: German and English
- translatable into further languages
- new organization and colored text representation
- mini pictures to the messages
- recurring events are specially adjustable
- running off recurring events are now deleted
- all attitudes now also testable
- Bekuna start with inserted
- nationaltypical date and time representation
- holiday editor
- photo announcement
- data exchange with other AMIGA's over the data input window
- error corrections
- and much more besides...

***** version 2.1 (14.12.2005) *****

- computation and announcement of sunrise and sunset and more
- new adjustment possibilities
- the adjuster is now separate in Prefs and can also alone be started
- data exchange with "Windows" versions (BEKUNAPC/PEKUTER)
- retroactive messages with longer absence (e.g. vacation)
- many small corrections...

@endnode
@node eingabe "Input"

  @{b}Data enter@{ub}

These windows possess a speech blister assistance.

  @{" Birthdays        " link gein}
  @{" Past events      " link vein}
  @{" coming events    " link kein}
  @{" recurring events " link wein}
  -------------------
  @{" Holiday editor   " link holi}


  @{b}Data exchange with other AMIGA:@{ub}

A data file (Eventdata 1-4), which from another AMIGA comes, can into
an opened data input window be droped. All current and not yet
available data, are then added the list. Subsequently, the list must
be stored then.

@endnode
@node gein "Input birthdays"

  @{b}of birthdays@{ub}

Here first your first name and your date of birth must be entered.
(Your own data must absolutely at 1. Stand for place!)
Now further birthdays can be entered.

The sequence of the input does not have to be in the order of the birthdays.
Also several persons with the same date of birth can be entered.
All inputs must be confirmed with the RETURN key!

It opens a window with the following functions:

 @{u}first name:@{uu}

Here input the first name or complet name (e.g. Rodger or Rodger Waters)

 @{u}date of birth:@{uu}

Here input the date of birth.
(e.g. 25.4.1965 or 25/04/1965 or USA: 04/25/1965)
Date in the nationalusual format.

 @{u}picture button@{uu}

Here a photo can be selected by the person concerned.
This can be indicated then to a birthday message.
For regarding the photo, on an entry in the list click.
For remove a photo, click on the entry in the list and then on the picture button. In the selection of
files window click then on breaking off.
 
see also: @{" Other functions of the data input window " link fuein}

@endnode
@node vein "Input events" 

  @{b}past events@{ub}

Here past events (e.g. day of engagement can, wedding day etc..) are entered.
Also impersonal events (e.g. wedding day of parents) can be entered.

The sequence of the input does not have to be in the order of the
events. Also events with the same date can be entered.
All inputs must be confirmed with the RETURN key!

It opens a window with the following functions:

 @{u}event:@{uu}

Here input the event (e.g. wedding day)

 @{u}date:@{uu}

Here input the event date.
Date in the nationalusual format.

 @{u}type:@{uu}

Here the type: personal or impersonal

 @{u}picture button@{uu}

Here a suitable photo can be selected to the event.
This can be indicated then to a message.
For regarding the photo, on an entry in the list click.
For remove a photo, click on the entry in the list and then on the picture button. In the selection of files
window click then on breaking off.

see also: @{" Other functions of the data input window " link fuein}

@endnode
@node kein "Input events" 

  @{b}coming events@{ub}

Here input the coming events (e.g. dates, vacation, can holidays etc..)

The sequence of the input does not have to be in the order of the events.
Also events with the same date can be entered. All inputs must be confirmed with the RETURN key!

Events those did not already run off, in this list any more are not
indicated. They are deleted only if on "Save" clicks.

With "Type" "Once" for unique events is indicated and "Again" for recurring events.
Recurring events are registered automatically into this list and can be also corrected here, if the event shifts e.g.
because of a holiday.
See in addition also: @{" Recurring events " link wein}

It opens a window with the following functions:

 @{u}event:@{uu}

Here input the event (e.g. party etc..)

 @{u}date:@{uu}

Here input the date.
Date in the nationalusual format.
This can be entered also over the calendar. Click on "Calendar".
Now the date in the calendar can be selected. With close the calendar the date to the list one takes up.
The date may not be smaller than the current date!

see also: @{" Other functions of the data input window " link fuein}

@endnode
@node wein "Input events"

  @{b}recurring events@{ub}

Here can input the recurring events
(e.g. garbage disposal every 14 days, charwoman each week, etc..)

The sequence of the input does not have to be in the order of the
events. Also events with the same date can be entered.
All inputs must be confirmed with the RETURN key!

Events those did not already run off, in this list any more are not
indicated. They are deleted only if on "Save" clicks.

It opens a window with the following functions:

 @{u}event:@{uu}

Here input the event (e.g. garbage disposal)

 @{u}starting from date:@{uu}

Here entered starting from which day the event valid is.
The date input takes place in the nationalusual format.
This can be entered also over the calendar. Click on "Calendar".
Now the date in the calendar can be selected. When closing the calendar the date is taken up to the list.
The date may not be smaller than the current date!

 @{u}to date:@{uu}

Here entered up to which day the event valid is.
This can be entered also over the calendar.
This field can be also released (no space characters to enter!). Thus this event is infinitely valid.

 @{u}interval:@{uu}

Here select the recurrence period (e.g. each 2. Week)

 @{u}save:@{uu}

Thus the list is stored. The 1. Date of a new or changed entry
is registered into the list of the coming events. If this date ran off
then, the next date is computed automatically and registered into the
list of the coming events. These are marked there by "Again". (by it
is possible changing a date in the list of the coming events if e.g.
the garbage disposal, because of a holiday, comes one day later.)
Likewise also in the list of the recurring events, with "starting from
date", the next date is always registered and indicated.

see also: @{" Other functions of the data input window " link fuein}

@endnode
@node fuein "Input window functions"

  @{b}other functions of the data input window@{ub}

  @{u}the menu@{uu}

Over the menu the window size and/or the window position can be fixed.

"Window - Snapshot size"
Store only the size and the window fix in screen center are always opened.

"Window - Snapshot size and position"
Fix store the size and the position of the window.

"Window - UnSnapshot"
Deletes the stored values and the window in screen center in minimum size is opened.

"Window - Close"
The window closes latches. Changes are not stored.

  @{u}add:@{uu}

Thus a new entry is added to the list. Now the data can be entered.
The inputs must be confirmed with the RETURN key.
The date input in the nationalusual format.

  @{u}remove:@{uu}

Thus an entry can be removed. First an entry select and click then on removing.

  @{u}entry changing:@{uu}

Select and then in the lower fields around an entry to changing, first change an entry.

  @{u}Save:@{uu}

The list stores in such a way, like it is indicated and closes
the window. When storing also the window size and/or the window
position are stored, if already the window size and/or the window
position were stored before over the menu.

  @{u}Cancel:@{uu}

The window without the changes closes to store.

@endnode
@node holi "Holidays"

  @{b}holiday editor (HolidayEdit)@{ub}

The holidays, holidays and anniversaries for the current and the following year are computed with the first start by Bekuna and with beginning of a new yearly.

With the holiday editor holidays can be added, changed or removed.
After storing the version number of the holiday file is increased and computed Bekuna, with the next start, the holidays again.

@endnode
@node anzeige "Show Data"

  @{b}show data@{ub}

  The data display been made by the menu to "Show data".

        @{" The next to last system start " link vlsys}
        @{" Data preview                  " link dvor}
        @{" Sun/Moon computation          " link somo}
        --------------------------------
        @{" Holidays                      " link feier}
        --------------------------------
        @{" Birthdays and events          " link daus}

@endnode
@node vlsys "The next to last system start"

  @{u}the next to last system start@{uu}

Here the date and the time next to last system star width unit are indicated.
Thus it can be controlled whether someone used the computer in your absence.

@endnode
@node dvor "Data preview"

  @{u}data preview@{uu}

Here a preview is indicated on the two next events. This is particularly meaningful, if only short preliminary message period were adjusted. With holidays, are indicated only legal holidays.

@endnode
@node somo "sun and moon"

  @{u}sun and moon computations@{uu}

This menu option is disable!
Here a complete and exact computation can be indicated by sun and moon.
Who has interest in it, ask to @{"me" link autor}.

@endnode
@node feier "Show holidays"

  @{b}Holidays (year)@{ub}

Thus all of the program computed holidays, holidays, anniversaries and summer time beginning and end in correct sequence
for the current or the next year indicated. The holidays are computed and stored with the first program start and with beginning of a new yearly.

The program recognizes the country adjusted with Locale Prefs and computes the holidays for the country after the file Holiday.(Land).
This file can be worked on with @{"HolidayEdit" link holi}.

see also: @{" Other functions of the data display window " link fuaus}

@endnode
@node daus "Show birthdays and events"

  @{b}Show the entered data@{ub}

With these four menu options, one can be able to be indicated all entered birthdays and events, sorted according to date.

With all windows also the weekday is indicated to each date. With birthdays is it the birth weekday. With birthdays also the current age and the asterisk are indicated. With birthdays and past events, with click on an entry also the added picture indicated.

With events already run off an X is indicated. These are deleted, as soon as new events are entered.

see also: @{" Other functions of the data display window " link fuaus}

@endnode
@node fuaus "window functions" 

  @{b}other functions of the window@{ub}

The window is closed with the closing symbol or the button of
OK ONE.

  @{u}the menu@{uu}

Over the menu the window size and/or the window position can be fixed.

"Window - Snapshot size"
Store only the size and the window fix in screen center are always opened.

"Window - Snapshot size and position"
Fix store the size and the position of the window.

"Window - UnSnapshot"
Deletes the stored values and the window in screen center in minimum size is opened.

"Window - Close"
The window closes latches. Changes are not stored.

"Printing - Print list"
All indicated data print list. Before the expression one can be able to be shown a preview.
NOTE! Printer must be pressure ready.

@endnode
@node meld "event messages" 

  @{b}event messages@{ub}

The event messages are divided and by different mini picture or letters are marked into four ranges.

1st (G) birthdays and past events
2nd (E) coming and recurring events
3rd (F) holidays and anniversaries
4th (S) special messages and comments

If several events in one of the ranges 1 to 3, in the preliminary message period arise, then appears on the right of a cycle gadget and the messages are paged through automatically (if switched on).
With operation of a Cycle Gadgets automatic paging through is stopped.
Maximally 20 messages per range can be indicated. All messages are announced also into the coming year inside.

@endnode
@node pmenü "project menu"

  @{b}the project menu@{ub}

 @{u}Bubble help@{uu}

Thus the bubble help for all windows can be switched on or off.

 @{u}Read guide...@{uu}

This Guide opens.

 @{u}Snapshot window@{uu}

Thus the position of the main window can be fixed (not the size!).
Fixing of the size is not possible, since the window adapts to the messages automatically.

 @{u}UnSnapshot window@{uu}

Thus the position of the main window is released again and the window opens in screen center.

 @{u}Update all@{uu}

With selection of this menu option the window is closed, updated and again opened.
The opened BEKUNA window is updated automatically with changes of message.
 
 @{u}Clock adjust@{uu}

Thus the internal computer clock adjust correctly.
You must be in addition ONLINE ones! The time is read, evaluated by a neutral atomic clock time server and adjust the clock. Subsequently, a window indicates the deviation.

 @{u}Country information@{uu}

Indicate the Locale Prefs attitudes.

If wrong values are indicated, then this is to be corrected in the Locale Prefs.
With wrong currency in europe announcement, the euro update was not installed.

 @{u}About...@{uu}

Shows information to the program.

 @{u}Quit@{uu}

Terminates the program.

@endnode
@node einstell "Adjustments"

  @{b}BEKUNA-Prefs@{ub}

These windows possess a speech blister assistance (bubble help).

The prefs can be called in 2 variants.
1st from Bekuna, over the menu
2nd with BekunaPrefs in the Prefs drawer (even if Bekuna does not run).

  @{u}Start@{uu}

    @{" Start " link einstart}

  @{u}Appearance@{uu}

    @{" Generally    " link einall}
    @{" Background   " link einhi}
    @{" Fonts        " link einzei}
    @{" Colored text " link einfarb}

  @{u}Messages@{uu}

    @{" Preliminary messages " link einanz}
    @{" Tone message         " link einton}
    @{" Program start        " link einprog}


 @{u}Save@{uu}

Stores all attitudes. Subsequently, the main window is closed, updated and again opened.

 @{u}Use@{uu}

Undertakes all attitudes without it to store. Subsequently, the main window is closed, updated and again opened. Used attitudes are valid up to the next restart.

 @{u}Cancel@{uu}

That closes window, without the changed attitudes to taking over.

@endnode
@node einstart "Start Prefs" 

 @{b}Start@{ub}

Thus launch characteristics can be changed by Bekuna.

The initialization program for Bekuna is called Bekuna Autostart and should always remain in the stock starting UP drawer, even if Bekuna is not to be started automatically. Since otherwise wrong messages appear.

Always one adjusts after that boats to start, then Bekuna starts after each restart of the computer.

One adjusts only once on the day to start, then Bekuna starts only after first switching on of the computer on on the today's day and then only again on the next day, after the adjusted starting time.

One does not adjust automatically to start, then Bekuna only manual can be started, with the program Bekuna-Start.

A manual start can take place at any time and affected not automatic launch characteristics.

If several programs are out started of the WBStartup, then a starting delay can be stopped for Bekuna, so that Bekuna appears as the latter on the Workbench.

Additionally one can be also still asked whether BEKUNA is to be started or not.

@endnode
@node einall "Generally"

 @{b}General@{ub}

Here the marking of the messages with mini picture or letters can be switched off. Just as also the moon diagram and all waiting windows. That switch off the waiting windows is particularly with very fast systems 1 GHz recommended.

During the speech blister delay waerend value is indicated to the manipulation of the sliding bar of the 10 subject. Cannot be made unfortunately differently.

EFFECTS:

 @{u}Automatic show picture to messages@{uu}

If a picture were assigned to a message, then this is indicated automatically. Not suitably for slow computers! Also only
for small pictures suitably!

 @{u}Leaftingeffekt@{uu}

Hereby forwards, the text field will appear to a new message
briefly black.

@endnode
@node einhi "Background"

 @{b}Background@{ub}

Here background samples can be specified for the individual windows.
In activation of standard the background sample adjusted with ReAction Prefs is used.

@endnode
@node einzei "Fonts"

 @{b}Fonts@{ub}

Here character sets for the announcement can be selected. Who uses only a small screen resolution, here only small and narrow Fonts should select. The attitude of the styles of font (fat, italic and underlined) functions only with Outline Fonts (GCTimes/GCTriumvirate/LetterGothic).

@endnode
@node einfarb "Colored text"

 @{b}Colored text@{ub}

@{u}Text adjustment@{uu}

Activate the checkmark, if you want to use colored text and background. Select with text selection the kind of the text and whether you would like to change the text color or the background colour.

@{u}Color adjustment@{uu}

Select here from the pallette the desired color. Over it a preview is shown.

@{b}NOTE!@{ub}
The palette shows 256 colors, if the screen is not adjusted to fewer colors.
The color palette is not constant! The indicated colors depend also on the WB-Background-Picture. Some programs change also the color palette.
Select as only as possible colors of the first 32 and the last 4 colors.
The first 4 (0,1,2,3) and the last 4 colors depends on the attitudes in palette prefs.
The numbers of 17,18,19 depend on the pointer color.
The numbers of 4,5,6,7 depend on the MagicWB colors.

@endnode
@node einanz "Preliminary reports" 

 @{b}Preliminary message@{ub}

@{u}Preliminary message period@{uu}

Here can be adjusted, as far in advance events are announced.
The event is above selected and among them the pertinent preliminary report periods. One does not adjust in advance, then the event is announced only on the day concerned.

If too many events are announced at one time, it recommends to adjust itself the preliminary message periods smaller. Maximally 20 messages per group are indicated. Additionally a short sound can be played to each message. preliminary message periods for sound messages and program
starts cannot be more largely adjusted than for the text message.

If program start is activated only on the adjusted day, then programs are started only on the adjusted day. Otherwise each day, starting from the adjusted day.

Example:

1 day before a birthday is to be written email (with YAM).

Set in addition with program start the checkmark with other birthday.
Now select YAM. With click on test now to YAM one starts. YAM close
and at preliminary report period - event, other birthday select and
with program starts in advance the 1 day stop. If the checkmark is set
with program start only on the adjusted day, then YAM is started 1 day
before a birthday when the reasoning Bekuna. If the checkmark is not
set, then YAM is started 1 day before and also at the birthday.

@{u}Display@{uu}

Messages automatically leaf activated, then, with the simultaneous occurrence of messages, in a group, these are paged through automatically.

Messages activated after 15 sec. automatically continue to leaf, then automatic leafing is again continued, 15 sec. after a manual operation of the cyclebuttons.

If sound is activated with automatic leafing, then when automatic leafing to messages, which lie within the clay/tone preliminary report period, the pertinent sound message is played.

If sound is activated with manual leafing, then when manual leafing to messages, which lie within the clay/tone preliminary report period, the pertinent sound message is played.

@endnode
@node einton "Sound message" 

 @{b}Tone message@{ub}

Here a sound file can be selected to different events. Only short sounds select! Long sounds become after approx.. 1-2 seconds broken off. With test the clay/tone can be tested.

@endnode
@node einprog "Program start"

 @{b}Program start@{ub}

Here a program can be started with the occurrence of an event.
Only programs can be selected, which can be started also from the Shell. With test the start can be tested. The start takes place then in such a way, as adjusted with preliminary reports and only when terminating Bekuna.

Questions before a program start is activated, then before a program start it is asked whether the program is to be really started.

If program start is activated only after that boats, then a program is started, only when first starting by Bekuna (after that boats). With each further manual start of Bekuna, then no program start takes place.

Thus it makes also for sense to register "Genesis" or "Miami" with always with reasoning if one after the computer start first into the InterNet to go would like to look over e.g. after post
office.

@endnode
@node schnell "fast select buttons"

  @{b}Fast select buttons@{ub}

The functions of the fast calling buttons:

@{" C " link kalender} opens the calendar (only to the information).
(during the operation no date is changed.)
@{" H " link feier} shows the holiday list for the current year.
@{" L " link vlsys} shows the next to last system start.

@{" D " link dvor} shows a preview to the next events.
@{" O " link daus} shows the coming events.
@{" I " link kein} input of coming events.

The operation takes place with the mouse or with the same letters on the keyboard.

@endnode
@node kalender "Calendar"

The calendar serves for checking or with the input windows for enters the date.

@endnode
@node daaus "data exchange" 

@{u}Data exchange with other AMIGA@{uu}

@{" see data input " link eingabe}

@{u}Manual data exchange from BEKUNA to PEKUTER:@{uu}

Produce on the AMIGA a new drawer somewhere. Start BEKUNA.
Select in the BEKUNA start attitudes, with data exchange with PEKUTER, the path of this new drawer.
Terminate BEKUNA. Now the data are transmitted into the new drawer and them to rule itself there in the sublist Data. These files (Evdata1-4.txt) can be transferred now into the PEKUTER Data drawer. PEKUTER recognizes these automatically. 

@{u}Manual data exchange from PEKUTER to BEKUNA:@{uu}

Activate in PEKUTER data exchange. PEKUTER produces the files (Evdata1-4.txt) in the Data drawer.
Produce on the AMIGA a new drawer somewhere.
Start BEKUNA. Select in the BEKUNA start attitudes, data exchange with PEKUTER, the path of this new drawer. Terminate BEKUNA. Now the data are transmitted into the new drawer and them to rule itself there in the sublist DATA. Copy the files of PEKUTER into the Data drawer and replace there the already existing. Restart BEKUNA, and BEKUNA takes over the data.

With a constant manual data exchange in both directions, the same drawer can be used. Then only the files (Evdata1-4.txt) must be transferred to the PC and back. 

@{u}Automatic data exchange with PEKUTER, if the Amiga on an emulator (e.g. WinUAE) runs@{uu}

@{b}IMPORTANT!
Make first a backup copy of all data!@{ub}
BEKUNA: Copy the Eventdata1-4 (Rexx:Data)
PEKUTER: With the data protection

Before the first use of the automatic exchange the data should be adapted manually, otherwise it can come to overrun!

Select in the BEKUNA start attitudes the path of the PEKUTER file.
Activate also in PEKUTER automatic data exchange. When starting BEKUNA, the data will transfer these from PEKUTER to BEKUNA and when terminating BEKUNA or save new data, will become from BEKUNA to PEKUTER to transfer.

@endnode
@node allgemein "References to the program" 

  @{b}References to the program@{ub}

Bekuna is updated automatically, if messages change. The window is closed and again opened.
Time, date and mondphase are constantly updated.

Bekuna can become also Iconifiziert, and with renewed opening is
updated, if in the meantime the messages changed.

"Bekuna-Start" is the manual initialization program for Bekuna.rexx.
It can be copied arbitrarily often and thus can Bekuna, from several places be started.

Bekuna can only started 1x become. With starting restart it is brought into
the foreground.

-----------------------------------------------

I wish you much fun with this program and am grateful for criticism, error messages, improvement suggestions and references to programming.

@endnode
@node problem "Problems"

  @{b}Which do for problems?@{ub}

BEKUNA runs only correctly, with a completely installed operating system. Startup Sequence examine! User Startup examine!

With OS3.5 and OS3.9 ClassAct may not be installed!

RexxMast must run. It must be started of the Startup Sequence out.
It must the entry:
SYS:System/REXXMast >NIL:
or
REXXMast >NIL:
in the Startup Sequence available its.
This entry may be only once available and not specially still in the user Startup!
RexxMast must be in the listing SYS:System. Not in the WBStartup!

Some errors are caused also by Patch programs. These cannot be tested.

Most problems come by programs, which are started in the Startup
Sequence, user Startup or WBStartup.

  @{u}System tests@{uu}

In archives also the drawer "Tests" is contained. This contains 3 test routines. The test results are then in the RAM disk. For problems, dispatch to @{"me" link autor} please these results.

  @{u}Acquaintance of problems@{uu}

Bekuna does not run, while PerfectPaint runs.

@endnode
